# 🚨 Day 3 — Real-World Scenario: Failed Login Investigation

## 📌 Scenario
While monitoring system logs, I investigated authentication activity to identify potential failed login attempts and suspicious access.


## 🎯 Objective
- Analyse system logs  
- Identify failed login attempts  
- Understand authentication behaviour  
- Practice real-world security monitoring  


## 🛠️ Commands Used

```bash
sudo cat /var/log/auth.log
sudo less /var/log/auth.log
sudo tail -f /var/log/auth.log

🔍 Investigation Steps
1. Viewed Authentication Logs
sudo cat /var/log/auth.log

✔ Observed system login activity
✔ Found authentication-related entries

2. Analysed Logs in Detail
sudo less /var/log/auth.log

✔ Scrolled through logs
✔ Identified suspicious entries

3. Monitored Logs in Real-Time
sudo tail -f /var/log/auth.log

✔ Observed live login attempts
✔ Checked for repeated failures
